StandardDescription: Cite evidence within text to: explain the influence of cultural, historical, social and political context on characters, setting, and plot development.
Compare and contrast the treatment of similar themes, topics, and patterns of events depicted in diverse modalities.
Analyze and provide evidence of how the author’s choice of purpose and perspective shapes content, meaning, and style.
Compare and contrast a primary and secondary account of the same event or topic.
Explain how the author’s choice of the point of view of a narrator or character impacts content, meaning, and how events are described.
